HEADWORD: pearly everlasting
<hw>pearly everlasting</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>an
American everlasting (<spn>Anaphalis margaritacea</spn>) having foliage
with soft wooly hairs and corymbose heads with pearly-white scarious
involucres.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cottonweed, Anaphalis margaritacea.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+MW10</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pearly-white</ent>⟦br⟧
